paragraphs.body: Rose started in theater at the age of five, in a community production of the musical Annie, in which she played Molly, and later played Gretl in the Sound of Music at Poway Performing Arts. For the next three years, she played a "Who" in The Grinch Who Stole Christmas at the Old Globe under the direction of Jack O'Brien. After Grinch, she went on to three years at The American Girl Revue Theater in Los Angeles, playing the American Girl doll Molly. She also started doing voice-overs for film, TV, and radio.

paragraphs.body: Rose relocated to Los Angeles in 2011 and is studying and auditioning for on camera film and TV roles. She was seen in The Young and The Restless, iCarly, Pretty Little Liars, as well as a number of TV commercials. She is also a singer, with a love of pop and Broadway, a dancer, and a Dean's List student. Julianna has a sister, Jennessa Rose, who is also an actress.
